channel.title: Chinese Bot - The low down
channel.description:
Through sheer luck, My sister has a Chinese exchange student round. He's male, and so Him and I get along quite well. We were on the computer, and I thought of the R-Bot website. (Game4RS.com). So, I had him translate it a bit, but his English isn't too good:
Handles all randoms Has Anti-Detection modules Uses Plugins
There isn't a scripting community for it as far as we can see, but, on the site it says stuff such as:
Auto Woodcuts, Auto Mines, and 'Other Functions'.
You buy auths ("Landing Points") per USE.
It's written in Java.
"The team is formed by the senior professional players and administrators, with outstanding development capabilities, our aim is to provide you the most professional Rs Autobot around"
It seems they never knew about the RS engine update.
Sadly, this bot exists, and it works (The trial does).
:rolleyes:
